⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Nox Owen
node M1 · M1 · ⟦Nox Owen:M1:8c82f7⟧

WHO   — Nox Owen — Thief of Perranth
WHAT  — A contender of Throne of Glass — a charming, light-fingered competitor who trains and jokes alongside Adarlan's Assassin, and who is wise enough to walk away from the contest with his life when the warning comes.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a thief steals to live, not to die; because survival is its own kind of skill; because the smart play, when champions start turning up dead, is to take the road out of Rifthold rather than the prize.
HOW   — By nimble hands and an easy tongue, by the street-cunning of a thief who reads a room and a man; by the good sense to trust Celaena's quiet warning and leave before the killings reach him.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I'm a thief, not a fool — and a thief knows when the smart move is the door.

